# ğŸ§  **Concepts Used (Summary)**

| Concept            | Description                                 |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| **Database**       | Logical grouping of tables.                 |
| **Table**          | Structure holding data in rows and columns. |
| **Primary Key**    | Unique identifier for each record.          |
| **Auto Increment** | Auto-generates sequential IDs.              |
| **Insert**         | Adds data to a table.                       |
| **View**           | Virtual table created from a SELECT query.  |
| **CASE**           | Conditional logic used inside SELECT.       |
| **Index**          | Optimizes performance for search queries.   |
| **Sequence**       | Generates unique numeric values.            |

---

# ğŸ“ **Viva / Oral Questions**

| Question                                       | Answer                                                                  |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| What is a View?                                | A virtual table that shows results of a stored query.                   |
| Why do we use a View?                          | To simplify complex queries and show summarized or restricted data.     |
| What is an Index?                              | A data structure that speeds up searching and sorting operations.       |
| How does AUTO_INCREMENT work?                  | It automatically increases the ID for each new inserted record.         |
| Can we insert into a View?                     | Yes, if the view is based on a single table and not an aggregate query. |
| What is the difference between View and Table? | A table stores data physically, while a view stores a query definition. |
| Why is Sequence commented out?                 | Because AUTO_INCREMENT already handles unique IDs in MySQL.             |
| What is the datatype of grades?                | DECIMAL(4,2) â€” allows up to 4 digits with 2 after the decimal.          |
| What is the use of CASE in SQL?                | To perform conditional logic like IFâ€“ELSE.                              |
| Why create an Index on `student_name`?         | For faster lookup and filtering by name.                                |

